==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crosshead
<hw>Cross"head`</hw> <pr>(-h?d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>
<def>A beam or bar across the head or end of a rod, etc., or a block
attached to it and carrying a knuckle pin; as the solid crosspiece
running between parallel slides, which receives motion from the piston
of a steam engine and imparts it to the connecting rod, which is hinged
to the crosshead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>crossheading</ent>⟦br⟧
